org.rsna.ctp.objects

Class ZipObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rsna.ctp.objects.FileObject
      • org.rsna.ctp.objects.ZipObject

  • public class ZipObject
extends FileObject
    A generic Zip object for collections of clinical trials data, providing parsing and access to the files. This object supports a manifest, the primary purpose of which is to provide a unique identifier along the same lines as the DICOM SOP Instance UID. The manifest is an XML file named "manifest.xml" stored in the root of the zip directory structure. The root element of the manifest can have any element name, but the UID must be an attribute of the root element and have the name "uid".

    This object can be used to access zip files not having a manifest, but in that case, all the manifest access methods return either null Strings or null XML documents (depending on the method).

    The schema of the manifest is: 

     <manifest
        uid="UID of the ZipObject instance"
        study-uid="UID of the study instance"
        date="YYYYMMDD"
        version="manifest version identifier"
        type="type of ZipObject"
        description="description of the ZipObject"
        pt-name="Last^First^Middle"
        pt-id="...">
    ...child elements as required for the usage of the ZipObject...
 </manifest>

      • getValue

        public java.lang.String getValue(java.lang.String path)
        Get the value of the node identified by a path in the manifest. This method is a convenience method that can only be relied on if the path to the node can be found by taking the first element matching each step of the path.
        Parameters:
        path - the path from the root element to the node. Note that this method uses the XmlUtil.getValueViaPath(String) method, and the path syntax is slightly different from that of XPath. Specifically, attributes are identified as "node@attribute" rather than "node/@attribute".
        Returns:
        the value, or the empty string if the node identified by the path is missing.

      • extractAll

        public boolean extractAll(java.io.File dir)
        Unpack the ZipObject using the directory structure of the zip file.
        Parameters:
        dir - the directory into which to unpack the zip file. This becomes root directory of the file tree of the object. Files with no path information are placed in this directory; files with path information are placed in child directories with this directory as the root. Directories are created when necessary.
        Returns:
        true if the operation succeeded; false otherwise.

      • extractFile

        public boolean extractFile(java.util.zip.ZipEntry entry,
                  java.io.File dir)
        Unpack the file corresponding to a ZipEntry and place it in a specified directory. If the directory does not exist, it is created.
        Parameters:
        entry - the entry pointing to the desired file in the zip file. This can be one of the entries in the array returned by getEntries().
        dir - the directory into which to unpack the zip file. This becomes root directory of the file tree of the object. Files with no path information are placed in this directory; files with path information are placed in child directories with this directory as the root. Directories are created when necessary.
        Returns:
        true if the operation succeeded; false otherwise.

      • extractFile

        public boolean extractFile(java.util.zip.ZipEntry entry,
                  java.io.File dir,
                  java.lang.String name)
        Unpack the file corresponding to a ZipEntry and place it in a specified directory with a specified file name. No path information from the Zip Entry is used. If the directory does not exist, it is created. If the ZipEntry is a directory, nothing is done and false is returned.
        Parameters:
        entry - the entry pointing to the desired file in the zip file. This can be one of the entries in the array returned by getEntries().
        dir - the directory into which to unpack the zip file.
        name - the file name for the unpacked file.
        Returns:
        true if the operation succeeded; false otherwise.
